---
description: Nx project name must match package.json name when project.json exists
alwaysApply: true
---

# Nx project and package name parity

When a package has `project.json`, its `name` field **must** exactly match the `name` field in that package's `package.json`.

```json
// packages/editor/project.json
{ "name": "@lambda/editor" }

// packages/editor/package.json
{ "name": "@lambda/editor" }
```

- Scaffolding: set both to the scoped npm name (e.g. `@lambda/editor`), not a short name like `editor`.
- Renaming: update `project.json`, `package.json`, and any `nx` commands / CI that reference the project.
- If there is no `project.json` (Nx config inlined in `package.json` only), this rule does not apply.
